body:
After the PR #5759 and PR #5802 , unpacked struct's constrained random has been supported by Verilator.

So, we can now return to a previously pending issue—the **structArray** case, which involves the constrained randomization of an array composed of struct data.

For example:

```
class StructArray;

    typedef struct {
        rand int arr[3];
        rand int a;
        rand bit [3:0] b;
        bit c;
    } struct_t;
    rand struct_t s_arr[2];

    constraint c_structArray_0 {
        foreach (s_arr[i])
            foreach (s_arr[i].arr[j])
                s_arr[i].arr[j] inside {[0:9]};
    }
    constraint c_structArray_1 {
        foreach (s_arr[i]) s_arr[i].a inside {[10:20]};
    }
```



We are currently working on this, and a PR is expected soon.

